entries.text: Can everyone hear me? It's the Elite Shrine Maiden Idol, Sakura Miko!
So, take a look at this, everyone. For the "Room Where You Can't Leave Until You Beat Miko,"
which we haven't done in quite a while... we actually renovated the room!
We did some construction work. It's looking a bit luxurious now.
We have a proper door now, too.
I think it's looking pretty good.
We can still add more, but...
We were actually running out of frames.
Last time... the last battle was with Shion-tan.
Umm, we could only place about five frames last time.
So this time, we made it so we can place a lot more.
That's why we did the renovations.
It's not an automatic door, okay? This exit on the side here.
This isn't an automatic door, alright?
Yes, umm... Aqua-tan is here too.
There may or may not be cases where...
Will be added to the wall.
So please look forward to it.
I think it's time to call in today's guest.
Does this mean I can leave?
I heard it was an automatic door.
You thought "it wasn't an automatic door, wait what is an automatic door?" Ah, I get it.
Everyone was saying "Yeah, you can basically just leave on your own."
Well, it does look like I could leave.
Towa-sama, I posted the announcement today, you see.
And people were like, "That's a confirmed automatic door."
They were saying, "I can't see a future where Miko beats Towa-sama." Well, Towa doesn't really see a future where she loses either.
But Towa-sama, are you actually good at Clubhouse Games? Wait, aren't there barely any people good at Clubhouse Games?
No, there are! Obviously there are! It's a game!
Then let's ban Speed for today.
But today, in the Room Where You Can't Leave Until You Beat Miko, we'll be playing Clubhouse Games as usual.
We'll take turns choosing the games we want to play.
You *could* choose that one, but... you know, read the room a bit.
I feel like I'm being pressured right now.
So much pressure. I mean, an overwhelming victory... surely Towa-sama wants a good match too?
Nice to meet you, Towa-sama. Yeah, I'll try to read the room.
"Room Where You Can't Leave Until You Beat Miko" project...
It's been a while since I did it.
I feel like I haven't done many 1-on-1 collabs with.
I'm trying to invite them proactively.
I've wanted to invite you for a long time.
And I finally did. That's why I invited you.
I feel like in 2025, Towa-sama and I got a bit closer.
True. I get that. In 2025, it was sudden.
It took about 4 or 5 years, but the distance shrank.
Yeah, the distance shrank. It really did.
She's blushing! She's blushing! It shrank!
But I do have the impression we met up a few times and got closer.
The number of times we met increased.
The Tamagotchi thing left a deep impression.
You were happy about the Tamagotchi.
Where even is it now? The Tamagotchi.
Mikochi doesn't know where it is either?!
We were so hyped, saying "Let's play Tamagotchi together!"
We ended without ever breeding them. The Tamagotchis.
Tamagotchis have too healthy of a lifestyle. Those guys.
If they don't adjust to my schedule, it's impossible.
Wait, but Towa-sama, you were taking great care of it! Really carefully.
Then gradually I was like, "How much do you poop?!" and "How hungry are you?!"
It started becoming a burden, so I muted it.
Ah, true. Miko-chan couldn't take care of it at all.
I even decorated the Tamagotchi and everything.
The one that kept turning into Shigemi.
It kept turning into Shigemi and dying.
The other day, Roboco-senpai was playing Tamagotchi.
Around the planet... dead Tamagotchis become stars, right?
Apparently. Miko didn't know that. I didn't even know that much.
So, there were about 5 stars. Roboco-senpai's.
I was like, "Wait, you're killing them a lot... there's a lot of dead ones."
When I looked inside... they were all Shigemi. 80% Shigemi.
She said "It can't be helped." "It is what it is."
But now she was raising a cute Tamagotchi.
Someone else's Tamagotchi was a Star Shigemi-san too.
It actually makes me feel bad.
Actually, Shigemi-san is starting to look cute.
I think it started from there.
In the Room Where You Can't Leave Until You Beat Miko...
We usually look at a Profile Book next.
We actually renewed the Profile Book too!
Yeah, it's totally fine. Totally fine.
Sorry, but I really couldn't think of answers.
It's fine, everyone just writes whatever.
We'll look at that, talk a bit, and then battle.
Look at profiles for 50 mins, then 10 mins for the rest?
Don't screw with me! That's too fast!
You know, in the document Miko sent to Towa-sama beforehand...
Wait, sorry, I didn't see that. Which part?
Basically, just in case it ends too fast...
I thought there was a possibility.
The pattern where you say "One more time!"
So there's a possibility of a 5-match set.
Well, I think it'll be 3 matches though.
My apologies. My apologies. I was muted.
"You look like you can write on it." Stop that.
Can you see this? Towa-sama, can you see the screen distance?
OK. Then let's take a look immediately.
Oi, wait. By the way, for the categories...
First is Name, What you want to be called, Tag ideas...
Wait, I already added the hashtag.
Things you want to do with Miko...
Anything you want to consult about...
We'll go through it like that.
Let's look at the left side first.
It's starting to get painful lately.
Debuting at 17, how many years has it been?
"Maybe I should graduate high school soon."
It's not "soon"! You could be a working adult by now!
It's virtual, so anything goes, seriously!
I mean, Miko, you can do the 0.1 thing.
Mikochi, how old are you now?
Miko is, in a little bit, going to be 18.8 years old.
If it hits .10, it becomes 18.10 which is weird.
So I plan to round up. In 2 years, I'll finally be 19.
Yes, 17 years old with some internal conflict.
Yeah, after much thought, I put the circle (secret).
I see. So Miko is older.
You haven't revealed your blood type either?
Yeah, I've really never said my blood type until now.
Yeah. What type do you think I am?
Type A. A. A. A. A.
Wow~. I won't say, but I do get told I'm Type A a lot.
I mean, you're definitely Type A, Miko thinks.
But I haven't been told I'm Type A much in this activity/streaming...
Sorry, but for Hololive... compared to Hololive levels...
Don't look down on Hololive! "I am Type A~"
I see. My family and people who know me well don't think I'm Type A, but...
They have this image that I clean up and organize.
Compared to other members, Towa-sama seems like the type to organize.
Back in the Old Server, the HoloServer Minecraft...
I went into Towa-sama's room without permission and checked the chests without permission.
Mikochi, you can't organize, can you?
This isn't a diss or anything.
Doesn't it make you feel gross? That...
It's inefficient and hard to find things.
But Miko-chan wants to put things away immediately. Bam bam bam.
So you're an Efficiency Freak in that regard.
Rather than cleaning, getting it off my person quickly is efficiency.
Right, reverse efficiency. An Efficiency Monster.
Eh, but isn't that inefficient in the end?
But when you do it yourself...
You kinda know, "I think I put it around here randomly."
I thought Towa-sama's room was beautiful.
After seeing Towa-sama's room for the first time, Miko-chan started cleaning her room more.
Ohh! How often do you clean?
It depends on my mental state. Depending on my mental state, there are times I don't do laundry for 1 or 2 weeks.
You know those huge Disney souvenir bags?
I've filled up about two of those before.
In the past... well, recently too...
My room has gotten pretty clean!
It was clean about 2 months after I moved.
You gave me a cute keychain, so I was grateful.
So Towa thought, "I'll return the favor when I go out," and bought a souvenir.
"I'm just dropping it off, so I'm coming over now."
About half your entrance space was buried.
Wait, you could walk in normally last time!
Is opening cardboard boxes a pain?
It's a pain, it's a pain.
True, I get it. It is a pain.
You have to break down the boxes.
Breaking them down is tough too.
So I just end up showing them off.
Don't swallow your words! I understood just now!
Since luck comes in through the entrance...
Also, they say you should keep water areas clean.
Wait, hair keeps falling out all the time.
Why is that? Am I going bald?
Every day, the sink is covered in hair.
Are you okay? Did you hear my worry?
It's gross after it falls out.
Hair on a person's head looks beautiful, shiny and all.
Just sitting there. It's really gross.
It's clean enough that you can come over anytime.
"What Towa wants to be called by Miko."
I don't know if Towa-sama noticed...
You did. When we meet in person, I say "Towa, Towa."
But sometimes "Towa-sama" slips out. Right now it's 50/50. I noticed it during that... Acorn Height Contest Minecraft.
Fishing Minecraft? The King Fishing Tournament thing.
"We are definitely going to be the Kings."
We were truly comical back then.
During the awards ceremony, I wanted to go off-screen.
I think Miko was saying "Towa" back then. I feel like I was.
If I think about it consciously.
It's been a long time, right?
You know, when you get close...
You get bored of the nickname.
You start calling them random things.
There was a time I was really lost.
I was calling her that for a bit.
It's gross. Being told "gross" was fun.
Sui-taya... that might be a bit gross.
I felt power go into your fist just now.
Please be prepared to be ignored when you do.
If you were to think of a Tag Name.
I didn't have any ideas. I thought about it a lot.
Wait, really? You thought about it?
It gave me really generic stuff, so I gave up.
Why did you say "Sakura and Tokoyami"?
How did you know? You checked, didn't you?!
It really gave me "Sakura and Tokoyami."
If we're going generic, maybe that.
Miko is really bad at thinking of hashtags.
Towa usually just asks everyone listening.
"Any good ideas?" I ask that a lot.
The commenters usually have good sense.
Chappy Yappy kind makes you want to say it.
But for Mikochi, that's a bit...
I think the level is too high.
Mikochi is really dog poo at FPS.
If I tried to boost you,
I can only see that future.
So if not an intense game...
So I picked what I'm into now.
What kind of game is this ARG?
You search for keywords you're curious about.
And arrive at the truth of the story.
You get a request like that.
You input the words you want to check.
The plot twists. There are a lot like that.
So when you play with someone...
You connect on voice chat and share screens?
Ah, that's right. Or you do it individually.
We search individually and input it into Excel or something.
Cool! I want to try that.
I don't know if you could keep up.
Miko usually fails the deduction though.
I get that. Towa is bad at deduction too.
It's easier to play than Werewolf.
We go into private rooms to talk and stuff.
Towa goes to a Pilates place, currently.
So you mix in with random people?
There are all kinds of people.
They say they do Pilates. Even models do it.
I see them do it. Pilates.
Apparently Tanaka Minami does it too.
But Towa-sama has high beauty standards.
Miko was surprised. You usually dress pretty rough.
But recently since winter started, Towa-sama has gotten fluffier.
When we met the other day, you had earmuffs? What was it?
You had pink Miffy ear warmers, like George.
I told you it was really cute.
It wasn't about cuteness, it was cold!
It was too cold. I can't let my ears get cold.
Can't expose them in winter. It's cold.
Conversely, I think Mikochi is more stylish.
When we go out, you wear cute skirts.
Here I am next to Subaru-chan, two jersey women.
Well, Subaru-chan is 80% jersey. You're stylish.
Every time, Subaru-chan is like, "Whoa, we match!" "We're matching!" And next to that, Mikochi is wearing cute clothes.
Is that so? Not at all, I just wear the same dresses.
Subaru-chan invited someone to Pilates once.
But they ended up not doing it.
Before going to Pilates, like last year...
We went to a hot spring.
We talked about Pilates being good.
"It's good! I wanna go, I wanna go!"
And she said recently, "I haven't invited her lately."
I asked why, and she said "I invited a few people who said they'd do it..."
"But people who don't do it, just don't do it."
"It's awkward with the teacher, so I stopped."
It feels like a higher hurdle.
I'm going with Bae and Bibi right now.
You do it at the same time?
I can work hard with someone next to me.
Seeing Bae and Bibi next to me...
I've been to the gym with people before.
But people seeing me gasp for air is really embarrassing.
Don't you want to not show your uncool side?
Before, it was tough so I took a break.
"It's your first time, so it's okay."
The motivation changed to "I'd be happy if I could do this move."
When I do it, I'll probably do something alone first.
Then say "I can do it now, let's go."
That pattern is more realistic for Miko.
If I don't do it with people, it doesn't happen.
Unless I make up my mind, it won't happen.
Contact me if you feel like it.
What I want to do with Miko.
Well, things to do with Mikochi...
Sorry, but I couldn't think of much.
Mikochi said that because she knows Towa likes FPS, even though she's bad at it.
"I'm bad, but Towa likes it, so I want to play." That's sweet, but hard.
Mikochi likes it, but Towa isn't good at it... Is that really entertaining?
I like seeing you get angry.
I like it when you get harsh.
You want to be scolded harshly?
Because being bad causes trouble for others.
I get it, I get it.
If one person is poop, it's tough balance-wise.
"Testing Luck" might be the perfect balance.
Yeah, luck testing is great. It's not about skill.
So I thought luck was better.
I wasn't pitiable at all though!
Miko wants to play a Horror Game.

So I thought that's how you were.
We started hanging out bit by bit.

When Towa-sama and Subaru combine, the extrovert energy is insane.
Miko still can't get used to it.
But now it's not like that.
Since we met, I felt we had to get along.
Or rather, I wanted to get along. That drive is amazing.
Is it? I mean, a cat tries hard to talk too, but...
I just think, "Wow, you said that." You're so socially capable.
"I talked to a girl for the first time."

You'll fall in love with Miko.
But let's not say too much.
It'll be hard to work later.

Others won't be able to interfere.
It's a secret just for here.
